ffirmed their commitments to working together to end discrimination and violence towards the LGBT community.<ref name=\"jurist.org\" /> UN High Commissioner for Human Rights [[Navi Pillay]] delivered remarks [press release] commending the LGBT community and praising the fact that, \"many countries have embarked on historic reforms\u2014strengthening anti-discrimination laws, combating hate crime against LGBT people and sensitizing public opinion.\"<ref name=\"jurist.org\" />\n** '''US Politics:'''\n*** '''[[Barack Obama]]''' mentioned the word \"gay\" and the issue of gay rights for the first time in a speech at the U.S. presidential swearing in; specifically, he did so in his inaugural address.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/obama-makes-history-citing-gay-rights-inaugural-address/story?id=18275341#.UaURH5zl6qg|title=Obama Makes History By Citing Gay Rights in an Inaugural Address - ABC News|date=2013-01-21|publisher=Abcnews.go.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref> \n*** On [[Celebrate Bisexuality Day]], the White House held a closed-door meeting with almost 30 bisexual advocates so they could meet with government officials and discuss issues of specific importance to the bisexual community; this was the '''first bi-specific event ever hosted by any White House'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bilerico.com/2013/09/in_historic_first_bi_activists_gather_at_white_hou.php|title=In Historic First, Bi Activists Gather at White House|date=25 September 2013|publisher=The Bilerico Project|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/08/22/white-house-to-hold-closed-door-session-on-bisexual-issues-next-month/|title=White House to hold closed-door session on bisexual issues next month|date=22 August 2013|work=The Washington Post/|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref>\n*** Rep. '''[[Mark Pocan]]''''s spouse '''Philip Frank''' became the first same-sex spouse of a federal lawmaker to officially receive a House Spouse ID.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lezgetreal.com/2013/05/rep-mark-pocans-husband-granted-congressional-spousal-id/|title=Rep. Mark Pocan's Husband Granted Congressional Spousal ID|date=2013-05-10|publisher=Lez Get Real|accessdate=2013-10-05|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007023932/http://lezgetreal.com/2013/05/rep-mark-pocans-husband-granted-congressional-spousal-id/|archivedate=7 October 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"huffingtonpost.com\">{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/10/mark-pocan-gay_n_3253487.html|title=Gay Congressman Makes History|last=Wing|first=Nicholas|date=10 May 2013|work=Huffington Post}}</ref> In 2009, '''Marlon Reis''', the spouse of Rep. '''[[Jared Polis]]''' (D-Colo.), was issued a congressional spouse ID, but later card services told him that he had been given the designation accidentally.<ref name=\"huffingtonpost.com\" />\n*** The U.S. Senate confirmed '''Nitza Qui\u00f1ones Alejandro''' to a federal judgeship, making her the first openly gay Latina to hold such a post.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/society/law/2013/06/13/first-out-lesbian-latina-confirmed-federal-judgeship|title=First Out Lesbian Latina Confirmed to Federal Judgeship|last=Ring|first=Trudy|date=2013-06-13|publisher=Advocate.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref>\n*** U.S. Air Force Under Secretary '''[[Eric Fanning]]''' took over as acting secretary of the U.S. Air Force, becoming the highest ranking openly LGBT official at the Department of Defense; he is openly gay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lgbtqnation.com/2013/06/first-out-gay-man-takes-over-as-acting-secretary-of-the-u-s-air-force/|title=First out, gay man takes over as Acting Secretary of the U.S. Air Force \u2013 LGBTQ Nation|date=2013-09-22|publisher=Lgbtqnation.com|accessdate=2013-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007002324/http://lgbtqnation.com/2013/06/first-out-gay-man-takes-over-as-acting-secretary-of-the-u-s-air-for