r-serve-white-house-lgbt-liaison/|title=First Woman of Color to Serve White House as LGBT Liaison|work=The Rainbow Times - Boston LGBT Newspaper Serving New England - Gay News|accessdate=15 November 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141114143529/http://www.therainbowtimesmass.com/2014/11/11/first-woman-color-serve-white-house-lgbt-liaison/|archivedate=14 November 2014|df=dmy}}</ref> She replaced '''[[Monique Dorsainvil]]''' who had served as the temporary liaison after '''Gautam Raghavan''' resigned.<ref name=\"Raghavan resignation\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.metroweekly.com/2014/09/white-house-lgbt-liaison-to-depart-administration/|title=White House LGBT liaison to depart Obama administration|date=4 September 2014|magazine=Metro Weekly|location=Washington, DC|last1=Snow|first1=Justin|accessdate=17 September 2015}}</ref>\n*** '''Gypsy Vered Meltzer''' was elected to the City Council in Appleton; as such he became the first openly transgender elected official in Wisconsin.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/transgender/2014/04/03/wisc-man-becomes-states-first-trans-elected-official|title=Wisc. Man Becomes the State's First Trans Elected Official|last=Marie|first=Parker|date=2014-04-03|publisher=Advocate.com|accessdate=2014-05-18}}</ref>\n* '''Costa Rica''' flew the gay pride flag at their presidential palace; the [[International Gay and Lesbian Human Rights Commission]] said the organization believed it was the first time the gay pride flag had been flown from the offices of a head of state in the Americas.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2014-05-16/features/sns-rt-us-costarica-gay-20140516_1_presidential-palace-rainbow-flag-lesbian-couple|title=Costa Rica to offer medical benefits to same-sex couples|work=tribunedigital-chicagotribune|accessdate=14 March 2015|date=23 May 2014}}</ref>\n* '''Cyprus' first ever gay pride parade''' draws several thousands of participants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://