deed the first openly LGBT person elected as such).'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/11/09/people-are-celebrating-women-who-made-history-on-us-election-nig/|title=People are celebrating women who made history on US Election night in response to Donald Trump win|date=2016-09-08|publisher=Telegraph.co.uk|first=Helena|last=Horton|accessdate=2016-11-09}}</ref>\n** [[Indonesia]]'s president [[Jokowi]] stated that he is defending the protection of LGBT rights in Indonesia<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2016/10/20/indonesia-president-jokowi-defends-lgbt-rights|title=Indonesia President Jokowi Defends LGBT Rights &#124; Human Rights Watch|date=|publisher=Hrw.org|accessdate=2016-12-15}}</ref>\n** [[Katherine Zappone]] became '''Ireland's first openly lesbian minister.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishcentral.com/news/Irelands-first-lesbian-govt-minister-a-US-native-makes-history-VIDEO.html|title=Ireland's first lesbian govt. minister, a US native, makes history (VIDEO)|date=7 May 2016|first=Dara|last=Kelly|work=IrishCentral.com}}</ref>\n** For the first time '''two openly gay men ran for parliament in [[Russia]].'''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/two-openly-gay-men-are-running-parliament-russia-election-putin-a7315181.html|title=Two openly gay men are running for parliament in Russia|newspaper=The Independent|first=Harriet|last=Agerholm|accessdate=2016-09-21}}</ref>\n** Australian Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull became the first sitting Australian Prime Minister to attend the '''Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras,'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/nsw/sydney-gay-and-lesbian-mardi-gras-feathers-glitter-and-stilettos-abound-as-revellers-prepare-for-38th-annual-parade-20160305-gnbh3s.html#ixzz428ao8yIDM|title=Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras: feathers, glitter and stilettos abound as revellers prepare for 38th annual parade|work=The Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref> also attended by Opposition Lea