ector to be nominated for any Academy Award.'''<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n**'''[[Daniela Vega]]''' became the first openly transgender person in history to be a presenter at the [[Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fuse.tv/2018/02/daniela-vega-presenting-oscars-openly-transgender-latinx-presenter|title=Daniela Vega as the Oscars' First Openly Transgender Presenter Is a Win for the LGBTQ and Latinx Communities|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"REhistory\">{{cite web|url=http://remezcla.com/film/daniela-vega-oscar-presenter/|first=Manuel|last=Betancourt|title=Transgender Actress Daniela Vega to Make History By Presenting at the Oscars|publisher=remezcla.com|date=17 February 2018|accessdate=18 February 2018|url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415044508/http://remezcla.com/film/daniela-vega-oscar-presenter/|archivedate=15 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Maya |last=Oppenheim |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/daniela-vega-oscars-2018-first-openly-transgender-presenter-a-fantastic-woman-star-a8240691.html%3famp |title=Daniela Vega: Star of A Fantastic Woman makes Oscars history as first openly transgender presenter |newspaper=The Independent |date=2018 |accessdate=2018-03-08}}</ref>\n**'''[[Marvia Malik]]''' became the first openly transgender newsreader to appear on Pakistani television in 2018.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-43544146|title=Pakistan TV airs first transgender anchor|last=Hamdani|first=Raza|date=2018-03-26|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-03-27|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.voanews.com/a/in-pakistan-news-anchor-makes-news/4315647.html|title=In Pakistan News Anchor Makes News|last=Ahmad|first=Asad|work=VOA|access-date=2018-03-27|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/03/27/asia/pakistan-transgender-anchor-intl/index.html|title=Pakistan gets its first transgender news anchor|first=Sophia |last=Saifi|work=CNN|access-date=2018-03-27}}</ref>\n**[[Peppermint (drag queen)|Peppermint]] made her [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] debut in [[The Go-Go's]]-inspired musical ''[[Head Over Heels (musical)|Head Over Heels]]''. The show began previews on 23 June 2018 and officially opened 26 July; playing the role of Pythio, '''Peppermint became the first trans woman to originate a principal role on Broadway.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/rupauls-drag-race-star-peppermint-will-make-her-broadway-debut-in-go-gos-musical-head-over-heels|title= RuPaul's Drag Race Peppermint Will Make Her Broadway Debut in Go-Go's Musical Head Over Heels|first=Ryan|last=McPhee|work=[[Playbill (magazine)|Playbill]]|date=29 January 2018|access-date=5 February 2018|archive-date=3 February 2018|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180203205159/http://www.playbill.com/article/rupauls-drag-race-star-peppermint-will-make-her-broadway-debut-in-go-gos-musical-head-over-heels |url-status=live}}</ref>\n**'''[[Christine Hallquist]] became the first openly transgender candidate for governor nominated by a major political party in the United States''' when she was nominated for governor of Vermont by the Democrats.<ref name=\"abcnews.go.com\"/>\n**'''[[Yance Ford]]''' and Joslyn Barnes were awarded an Emmy for Exceptional Merit in Documentary Filmmaking for producing ''[[Strong Island (film)|Strong Island]]'', which made Ford the first openly transgender man and the first black openly transgender person to win an Emmy award, as well as the first openly transgender filmmaker to win a [[Creative Arts Emmy]].<ref name=\"Intomore.com\"/><ref name=\"Emmys.com\"/><ref name=\"dl\"/>\n**'''Patricio Manuel''' became the first openly transgender male to box professionally in the United States, and, as he won the fight, the first openly transgender male to win a pro boxing fight in the U.S.<ref name=\"si.com\"/>\n**'''Colombia''' prosecuted a transgender woman's murder as a [[femicide]] for the first time in 2018, sentencing Davinson Stiven Erazo S\u00e1nchez to twenty years in a psychiatric center for \"aggravated femicide\" a year after he killed Anyela Ramos Claros, a transgender woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/first-time-colombia-prosecutes-transgender-woman-s-murder-femicide-n950021 |title=For the first time, Colombia prosecutes a transgender woman's murder as a femicide |publisher=Nbcnews.com |date= |accessdate=2018-12-23}}</ref>\n\n==2019==\n<!--Please also add applicable entries to the List of lesbian, gay, bisexual, or transgender firsts by year article-->\n* '''Same-sex marriage laws''':\n**'''Came into effect''': [[Same-sex marriage in Austria|Austria]]\n**'''Passed and came into effect''': [[Same-sex marriage in Taiwan|Taiwan]] (first in Asia); Mexican states of [[Same-sex marriage in San Luis Potos\u00ed|San Luis Potos\u00ed]], [[Same-sex marriage in Hidalgo|Hidalgo]] and [[Same-sex marriage in Baja California Sur|Baja California Sur]]\n**'''Supreme court ruling''': [[Same-sex marriage in Ecuador|Ecuador]] and Mexican states of [[Same-sex marriage in Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Nuevo Le\u00f3n]] and [[Same-sex marriage in Aguascalientes|Aguascalientes]]\n*'''Civil union laws:'''\n**'''Came into effect:''' [[Recognition of same-sex unions in San Marino|San Marino]]\n**'''Passed:''' [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Monaco|Monaco]]\n**'''Court order not yet implemented and subject to appeal:''' [[Same-sex marriage in the Cayman Islands|Cayman Islands]]\n* '''Decriminalisation of homosexuality''': [[LGBT rights in Angola|Angola]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2019/01/23/angola-decriminalizes-same-sex-conduct |title=Angola Decriminalizes Same-Sex Conduct &#124; Human Rights Watch |publisher=Hrw.org |date= |accessdate=2019-02-28}}</ref> [[LGBT rights in Botswana|Botswana]]\n* '''Criminalisation of homosexuality passed or came into effect''': [[LGBT rights in Brunei|Brunei]], [[Gabon]]<ref>{{Cite web|u