izes national and international evidence and brings out recommendations for bisexual inclusion in the future.<ref name=\"bisexualityreport\" />\n\n==2013==\n* '''Same-sex marriage laws''':\n** '''Passed and came into effect''': [[Same-sex marriage in New Zealand|New Zealand]], [[Same-sex marriage in Uruguay|Uruguay]], [[Same-sex marriage in France|France]], [[LGBT rights in Brazil|Brazil]], the U.S. states of [[Same-sex marriage in Delaware|Delaware]], [[Same-sex marriage in Rhode Island|Rhode Island]], [[Same-sex marriage in Minnesota|Minnesota]], [[Same-sex marriage in New Jersey|New Jersey]], [[Same-sex marriage in Hawaii|Hawaii]] and [[Same-sex marriage in New Mexico|New Mexico]], the [[Same-sex marriage in the Confederated Tribes of the Colville Reservation|Confederated Tribes of the Colville Reservation]], the [[Same-sex marriage in the Little Traverse Bay Bands of Odawa Indians|Little Traverse Bay Bands of Odawa Indians]], the [[Same-sex marriage in the Pokagon Band of Potawatomi Indians|Pokagon Band of Potawatomi Indians]], the [[Same-sex marriage in the Cheyenne and Arapaho Tribes|Cheyenne and Arapaho Tribes]], the [[Same-sex marriage in the Leech Lake Band of Ojibwe|Leech Lake Band of Ojibwe]], the [[Same-sex marriage in the Grand Portage Band of Chippewa|Grand Portage Band of Chippewa]] and the [[Same-sex marriage in the Iipay Nation of Santa Ysabel|Iipay Nation of Santa Ysabel]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldonline.com/2013/06/24/4971450/california-native-american-tribe.html|title=California Native American Tribe Announces Support of Same Sex Marriage: Santa Ysabel Tribe First in California to Make Proclamation|date=2013-06-24|publisher=Rock Hill Herald Online|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130628034639/http://www.heraldonline.com/2013/06/24/4971450/california-native-american-tribe.html|archive-date=28 June 2013|url-status=dead|accessdate=2013-06-25|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pokagonband-nsn.gov/sites/default/files/assets/group/tribal-council/form/2013/marriage-code-3-9-13-1369-1173.pdf|title=POKAGON BAND OF POTAWATOMI INDIANS MARRIAGE CODE|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wwmt.com/news/features/featured/stories/west-michigan-couple-have-first-samesex-wedding-pokagon-tribal-court-1278.shtml|title=West Michigan couple have first same-sex wedding in Pokagon Tribal Court|date=2013-06-21|publisher=WWMT Newschannel 3|accessdate=2013-06-25|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627233914/http://wwmt.com/news/features/featured/stories/west-michigan-couple-have-first-samesex-wedding-pokagon-tribal-court-1278.shtml|archivedate=27 June 2013|df=dmy}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wenatcheeworld.com/news/2013/sep/07/colvilles-recognize-same-sex-marriage/|title=Colvilles recognize same sex marriage|publisher=|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/marriage-equality/2013/03/15/michigan-native-american-tribe-recognizes-same-sex-marriage|title=Michigan Native American Tribe Recognizes Same-Sex Marriage|last=Rudolph|first=Christopher|date=15 March 2013|work=[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]|accessdate=16 March 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/gay-couples-hitched-minnesota-rhode-island-134316870.html|title=Gay couples get hitched in Minnesota, Rhode Island|date=1 August 2013|work=[[Yahoo News]]|accessdate=3 August 2013}}</ref> \n** '''Restored''': [[Same-sex marriage in California|California]]\n** '''Passed''': [[Same-sex marriage in the United Kingdom|England and Wales]] and US state of [[Same-sex marriage in Illinois|Illinois]]\n** '''Passed but then overturned''': [[Same-sex marriage in the Australian Capital Territory|Australian Capital Territory]]\n** '''Came into effect''': U.S. State of [[Same-sex marriage in Maryland|Maryland]]\n** '''Recognition''': The Supreme Court of the United States ruled Section 3 of [[Defense of Marriage Act]] unconstitutional, thus giving same-sex marriage federal recognition.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/06/26/supreme-court-doma-decision_n_3454811.html | work=Huffington Post | title=Supreme Court Rules DOMA Unconstitutional | date=26 June 2013 | first1=Ryan J. | last1=Reilly | first2=Sabrina | last2=Siddiqui}}</ref> US state of Oregon\n* '''Civil Union/Registered Partnership laws''':\n** '''Passed and came into effect''': Mexican state of [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Mexico|Campeche]]\n** '''Came into effect''': U.S. State of [[LGBT rights in Colorado|Colorado]]\n* '''Limited Partnership laws''':\n** '''Passed and came into effect''': [[LGBT rights in Costa Rica|Costa Rica]]\n* '''Same-sex couple adoption legalisation''': [[Same-sex marriage in New Zealand|New Zealand]] and [[Same-sex marriage in France|France]]\n* '''Recriminalisation of homosexuality''': [[LGBT rights in India|India]]\n* '''Anti-discrimination legislation''':\n** '''For sexual orientation and gender identity''': [[LGBT rights in Cyprus|Cyprus]] and [[LGBT rights in Puerto Rico|Puerto Rico]]\n** '''For gender identity''': US state of [[LGBT rights in Delaware|Delaware]]; and '''gender expression''': Canadian provinces of [[Newfoundland and Labrador]] and [[Prince Edward Island]]\n* '''Anti-discrimination executive action''':  US state of [[LGBT rights in Virginia|Virginia]]\n* '''First Pride Marches:''' In '''[[Ukraine]];'''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-22667015|title=Ukraine stages first gay pride march|date=25 May 2013|work=BBC News}}</ref> '''[[Montenegro]];'''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/10/20/montenegro-gay-pride-parade_n_4131778.html|title=Montenegro's First Gay Pride Parade Takes Place Under Heavy Security|last=Wong|first=Curtis|date=2013-10-20|publisher=Huffingtonpost.com|accessdate=2014-01-18}}</ref> and '''[[Curacao]]'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaycuracao.com/eng/curacao_pride.php|title=GAYCURA\u00c7AO.COM - We live and let live!|publisher=Gaycuracao.com|accessdate=2014-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023001355/http://www.gaycuracao.com/eng/curacao_pride.php|archive-date=23 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* '''Politics:'''\n** '''[[Kathleen Wynne]]''' became the first openly LGBT premier of a Canadian province, namely Ontario, after defeating Sandra Pupatello in the third round of voting of the Ontario Liberal party's leadership race on 26 January 2013. Sworn in on 11 February 2013, she is the party's first openly LGBT leader and Ontario's first female premier.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}}\n** '''[[Xavier Bettel]]''', '''first openly gay''' Prime Minister of Luxembourg, assumes office 4 December.\n** '''[[Etienne Schneider]]''', '''first openly gay''' Deputy Prime Minister of Luxembourg, assumes office 4 December.\n** '''[[Luxembourg]]''' becomes the first country in the world to have an openly gay Prime Minister [[Xavier Bettel]] and an openly gay Deputy Prime Minister [[Etienne Schneider]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2013/11/14/luxembourg-to-become-first-country-to-have-gay-prime-minister-and-gay-deputy-pm/ |title=Luxembourg to become first country to have gay prime minister and gay deputy PM \u00b7 PinkNews |publisher=Pinknews.co.uk |date=2013-11-14 |accessdate=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n** '''[[Nikki Sinclaire]]''' came out as transgender, thus becoming the [[United Kingdom]]'s first openly transgender Parliamentarian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2013/11/17/former-ukip-mep-reveals-she-is-the-uks-first-transgender-parliamentarian/|title=Former UKIP MEP reveals she is the UK's first transgender Parliamentarian \u00b7|date=2013-11-17|publisher=Pinknews.co.uk|accessdate=2014-01-18}}</ref> '''[[Daniel Kawczynski]]''' became the first MP in Britain to come out as bisexual.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/tory-mp-daniel-kawczynski-comes-out-as-bisexual-8680343.html|title=Tory MP Daniel Kawczynski comes out as bisexual|last=Legge|first=James|date=30 June 2013|work=The Independent|location=London}}</ref>\n** '''[[Benjamin Medrano]]''' was elected as the first openly gay mayor in Mexico's history, being elected mayor of the township of [[Fresnillo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/politicians/2013/07/19/rural-region-elects-mexicos-first-openly-gay-mayor|title=Rural Region Elects Mexico's First Openly Gay Mayor|last=Reynolds|first=Daniel|date=2013-07-19|publisher=Advocate.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref>\n** The '''first United Nations ministerial meeting on the rights of lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender individuals''' was held.<ref name=\"jurist.org\">{{cite web|url=http://jurist.org/paperchase/2013/09/first-un-ministerial-meeting-on-gay-rights-held.php|title=Paper Chase: UN holds first ministerial meeting on gay rights|date=2013-09-27|publisher=JURIST|accessdate=2014-01-18}}</ref> Representatives from the US, France, Argentina, Brazil, Croatia, the Netherlands, Norway, Japan, New Zealand and the EU, along with executive directors of [[Human Rights Watch]] and the [[International Gay and Lesbian Human Rights Commission]] reaffirmed their commitments to working together to end discrimination and violence towards the LGBT community.<ref name=\"jurist.org\" /> UN High Commissioner for Human Rights [[Navi Pillay]] delivered remarks [press release] commending the LGBT community and praising the fact that, \"many countries have embarked on historic reforms\u2014strengthening anti-discrimination laws, combating hate crime against LGBT people and sensitizing public opinion.\"<ref name=\"jurist.org\" />\n** '''US Politics:'''\n*** '''[[Barack Obama]]''' mentioned the word \"gay\" and the issue of gay rights for the first time in a speech at the U.S. presidential swearing in; specifically, he did so in his inaugural address.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/obama-makes-history-citing-gay-rights-inaugural-address/story?id=18275341#.UaURH5zl6qg|title=Obama Makes History By Citing Gay Rights in an Inaugural Address - ABC News|date=2013-01-21|publisher=Abcnews.go.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref> \n*** On [[Celebrate Bisexuality Day]], the White House held a closed-door meeting with almost 30 bisexual advocates so they could meet with government officials and discuss issues of specific importance to the bisexual community; this was the '''first bi-specific event ever hosted by any White House'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bilerico.com/2013/09/in_historic_first_bi_activists_gather_at_white_hou.php|title=In Historic First, Bi Activists Gather at White House|date=25 September 2013|publisher=The Bilerico Project|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/08/22/white-house-to-hold-closed-door-session-on-bisexual-issues-next-month/|title=White House to hold closed-door session on bisexual issues next month|date=22 August 2013|work=The Washington Post/|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref>\n*** Rep. '''[[Mark Pocan]]''''s spouse '''Philip Frank''' became the first same-sex spouse of a federal lawmaker to officially receive a House Spouse ID.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lezgetreal.com/2013/05/rep-mark-pocans-husband-granted-congressional-spousal-id/|title=Rep. Mark Pocan's Husband Granted Congressional Spousal ID|date=2013-05-10|publisher=Lez Get Real|accessdate=2013-10-05|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007023932/http://lezgetreal.com/2013/05/rep-mark-pocans-husband-granted-congressional-spousal-id/|archivedate=7 October 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"huffingtonpost.com\">{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/10/mark-pocan-gay_n_3253487.html|title=Gay Congressman Makes History|last=Wing|first=Nicholas|date=10 May 2013|work=Huffington Post}}</ref> In 2009, '''Marlon Reis''', the spouse of Rep. '''[[Jared Polis]]''' (D-Colo.), was issued a congressional spouse ID, but later card services told him that he had been given the designation accidentally.<ref name=\"huffingtonpost.com\" />\n*** The U.S. Senate confirmed '''Nitza Qui\u00f1ones Alejandro''' to a federal judgeship, making her the first openly gay Latina to hold such a post.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/society/law/2013/06/13/first-out-lesbian-latina-confirmed-federal-judgeship|title=First Out Lesbian Latina Confirmed to Federal Judgeship|last=Ring|first=Trudy|date=2013-06-13|publisher=Advocate.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref>\n*** U.S. Air Force Under Secretary '''[[Eric Fanning]]''' took over as acting secretary of the U.S. Air Force, becoming the highest ranking openly LGBT official at the Department of Defense; he is openly gay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lgbtqnation.com/2013/06/first-out-gay-man-takes-over-as-acting-secretary-of-the-u-s-air-force/|title=First out, gay man takes over as Acting Secretary of the U.S. Air Force \u2013 LGBTQ Nation|date=2013-09-22|publisher=Lgbtqnation.com|accessdate=2013-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131007002324/http://lgbtqnation.com/2013/06/first-out-gay-man-takes-over-as-acting-secretary-of-the-u-s-air-force/|archive-date=7 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*** '''[[Todd Hughes]]''' became the first openly gay U.S. circuit judge.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upi.com/Top_News/US/2013/09/24/First-openly-gay-US-circuit-judge-confirmed-by-Senate/UPI-27051380045847/|title=Todd Hughes, first openly gay U.S. circuit judge confirmed by Senate|publisher=UPI.com|accessdate=2014-01-18}}</ref>\n* '''Sports:'''\n** '''[[Robbie Rogers]]''' announced he was gay on 15 February 2013, becoming the only male fully capped international [[association football]]er to do so. He joined the Los Angeles Galaxy, making him the first openly gay male athlete to compete in [[Major League Soccer]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/25/sport/football/rogers-joins-galaxy/?hpt=hp_t2|title=Robbie Rogers becomes 1st openly gay man in U.S. pro soccer - CNN.com|date=27 May 2013|work=CNN}}</ref>\n** '''[[Jason Collins]]''' on 29 April 2013, became the first active male professional athlete in a major North American team sport to publicly come out as gay.\n** '''[[Fallon Fox]]''' came out as transgender, thus becoming the first openly [[transgender]] athlete in [[mixed martial arts]] history.<ref name=\"si20130307\">{{cite news|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/mma/news/20130307/fallon-fox-profile/|title=How Fallon Fox became the first known transgender athlete in MMA|last=Hunt|first=Loretta|date=7 March 2013|work=[[Sports Illustrated|SportsIllustrated]].[[CNN]].com|publisher=[[Time Inc.]]|accessdate=12 May 2013}}</ref>\n** '''Jallen Messersmith''' of [[Benedictine College]] in Atchison, Kan., came out and is believed to be the first openly gay player in U.S. men's college basketball.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/story/_/id/9322793/benedictine-college-basketball-player-jallen-messersmith-announces-gay|title=Benedictine College basketball player Jallen Messersmith announces he's gay - ESPN|date=2013-05-29|publisher=Espn.go.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref>\n** '''[[Cason Crane]]''' became the first openly gay man to summit the [[Seven Summits]] and the first to bring the rainbow flag to the summit of [[Mount Everest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sdgln.com/health/2013/06/12/first-openly-gay-man-cason-crane-conquers-mount-everest|title=First openly gay man conquers Mount Everest &#124; San Diego Gay and Lesbian News|publisher=Sdgln.com|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref>\n** The first UFC match between two openly gay fighters, '''[[Liz Carmouche]]''' and '''[[Jessica Andrade]]''', was held.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.towleroad.com/2013/07/liz-carmouche-wins-historic-ufc-match-between-two-openly-gay-fighters-video.html|title=Liz Carmouche Wins Historic UFC Match Between Two Openly Gay Fighters - VIDEO&#124; Gay News|publisher=Towleroad|accessdate=2013-10-05|url-status=dead