cessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref> Marianne van Praag, a Reform rabbi from The Hague, was the only rabbi aboard.<ref name=\"forward.com\">{{cite web|url=http://forward.com/articles/203478/flamboyant-first-as-jewish-boat-floats-in-amsterda/|title=Flamboyant First as Jewish Boat Floats in Amsterdam Gay Pride Canal Fest|date=4 August 2014|work=The Jewish Daily Forward|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jta.org/2014/08/04/news-opinion/world/aboard-amsterdams-jewish-gay-boat-activists-warn-against-tolerating-hate-1|title=Aboard Amsterdam's Jewish gay boat, activists warn against tolerating hate|work=Jewish Telegraphic Agency|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref> The '''first Moroccan boat also participated in the [[Amsterdam Pride]] Canal Parade.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2014/08/136244/moroccan-lgbt-boat-sails-in-amsterdam-gay-pride-canal-parade/|title=Moroccan LGBT Boat Sails in Amsterdam Gay Pride Canal Parade|work=Morocco World News|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref> \n** ''Cosmopolitan'' magazine, a women's magazine, offered '''sex advice to lesbians for the first time''' in its history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/rossalynwarren/cosmopolitan-has-launched-their-first-ever-lesbian-sex-posit|title=Cosmopolitan Has Launched Its First Ever Lesbian Sex Position Guide|first=Rossalyn|last=Warren|work=BuzzFeed|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref>\n** '''Pascal Tessier''', a 17-year-old from Chevy Chase, Md., became the first known openly gay Boy Scout to be an Eagle Scout.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/youth/2014/02/11/meet-first-openly-gay-eagle-scout|title=Meet the First Openly Gay Eagle Scout|first=Daniel|last=Reynolds|work=Advocate.com|accessdate=14 March 2015}}</ref>\n** The '''United Church of Christ''' was the first religious denomination to be a major sponsor of the [[Gay Games]], as a fourth-tier silver sponsor of Gay Games 9.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/sports/2014/08/09/ucc-becom