h the theme \"Bi the Way, Our Health Matters Too!\"; it included the first social media campaign to address disparities in physical and mental health facing the bisexual community.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glaad.org/blog/bi-way-our-health-matters-too-its-bisexual-health-awareness-month|title=\"Bi the way, our health matters too!\" \u2013 It's Bisexual Health Awareness Month!|date=2014-03-03|publisher=GLAAD|accessdate=2014-04-05}}</ref>\n* '''[[Queen Elizabeth II]]''' praised the [[London Lesbian and Gay Switchboard]] for their 40-year history making it the first time the Crown has ever publicly supported the LGBT community. They received a comment from the Queen saying: \"Best wishes and congratulations to all concerned on this most special anniversary.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.passportmagazine.com/blog/archives/35130-here-here-queen-elizabeth-makes-first-gesture-of-goodwill-to-the-lgbt-community/|title=Hear Hear Queen Elizabeth Makes First Gesture of Goodwill to the LGBT Community|date=2014-03-07|work=Passport Magazine|accessdate=2014-04-05|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151019104841/http://www.passportmagazine.com/blog/archives/35130-here-here-queen-elizabeth-makes-first-gesture-of-goodwill-to-the-lgbt-community/|archivedate=19 October 2015|df=dmy}}</ref>\n\n==2015==\n* '''Same-sex marriage laws''':\n** '''Passed and came into effect''': [[Same-sex marriage in the United States|United States]] [nationwide],<ref>{{cite web|title=Obergefell et al. v. Hodges, Director, Ohio, Department of Health, et al.|url=https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/14pdf/14-556_3204.pdf|website=supremecourt.gov|accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref>  the US state of [[Same-sex marriage in Florida|Florida]], the [[Same-sex marriage under United States tribal jurisdictions#Central Council of the Tlingit and Haida Tribes of Alaska|Central Council of the Tlingit and Haida Tribes of Alaska]], the [[Same-sex marriage under United States tribal jurisdictions#Oneid