le/2016/06/15/prince-william-makes-history-with-gay-magazine-cover/85918338/|title=Prince William makes history with gay magazine cover|date=|publisher=Usatoday.com|accessdate=2016-06-18}}</ref>\n*** Lord '''[[Ivar Mountbatten]]''' came out as gay and revealed that he was in a relationship with James Coyle, an airline cabin services director whom he met whilst at a ski resort in [[Verbier]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/17/queens-cousin-lord-ivar-mountbatten-has-spoken-of-his-decision-t/|title=Queen's cousin Lord Ivar Mountbatten has spoken of his decision to come out as gay after finding love|last=Harley|first=Sarah|date=17 September 2016|access-date=17 September 2016|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref> While not being a member of the British royal family, he is the first member of the extended family to come out as gay.<ref name=\"pinknewsfirstpersonintheroyal\">{{cite news|url=http://www.pinknews.co.uk/2016/09/18/the-first-person-in-the-royal-family-has-just-come-out-as-gay/|title=The first person in the royal family has just come out as gay|date=18 September 2016|work=Pink News|last1=Beresford|first1=Meka|accessdate=18 September 2016}}</ref>\n*** [[Carl Austin-Behan]] was sworn in as Manchester's '''first openly gay Lord Mayor.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.towleroad.com/2016/05/carl-austin-behan/|title=Meet Carl Austin-Behan, the Former Mr. Gay UK Just Sworn in as Manchester's Lord Mayor|last=Towle|first=Andy|date=18 May 2016|publisher=Towleroad|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref>\n*** [[Nicola Sturgeon]] becomes the first UK prime minister or First Minister to deliver an address at a Gay Pride event when she appeared at Glasgow Pride 2017. She addressed the crowd vowing to continue fighting for equality and respect throughout the UK, Closing with the statement \"Love is Love\".\n** '''US Politics:'''\n*** President Barack Obama appointed '''[[Raffi Freedman-Gurspan]]''' as the White House's primary LGBT liaison, making her the first openly transgender person in the role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/dominicholden/white-appoints-first-transgender-person-as-primary-lgbt-liai#.xoDEvzlOd|title=White House Appoints First Transgender Person As Primary LGBT Liaison|work=BuzzFeed}}</ref>\n*** '''[[Maite Oronoz Rodr\u00edguez]]''' became Puerto Rico's first openly gay chief justice and, as such, the first openly gay chief justice in U.S. history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://national.suntimes.com/national-world-news/7/72/2643689/puerto-rico-appoints-first-openly-gay-chief-justice/|title=Puerto Rico appoints first openly gay chief justice|date=23 February 2016|work=Sun-Times National|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202020358/http://national.suntimes.com/national-world-news/7/72/2643689/puerto-rico-appoints-first-openly-gay-chief-justice/|archivedate=2 February 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*** [[Eric Fanning]] became the '''first openly gay Secretary of the United States Army.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/eric-fanning-openly-gay-army-secretary_us_573b83a7e4b0646cbeeb47a0?section=politics|title=Senate Confirms First Openly Gay Army Secretary|date=2015-12-08|publisher=Huffingtonpost.com|accessdate=2016-05-18}}</ref>\n*** Santa Clara County became the '''first county government in the U.S. to raise the [[transgender pride flag]].'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ebar.com/news/article.php?sec=news&article=71398|title=The Bay Area Reporter Online - Santa Clara is first county in US to raise trans flag|work=Bay Area Reporter}}</ref>\n*** '''Trans United Fund''' was founded; it is the first group of its kind, a 501(c)(4) organization of transgender leaders focused on transgender issues.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/4287288/trans-united-transgender-politics-political-group/|title=Trans United Fund: Advocates Form Ambitious Political Group|work=TIME.com|first=Katy|last=Steinmetz}}</ref>\n*** '''[[Misty Plowright]]''' became the first openly transgender candidate to win a major party primary for the US House of Representatives.<ref name=\"theguardian1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/jul/04/transgender-nominee-congress-misty-plowright|title=Transgender nominee for Congress: 'It's about damn time' politics got inclusive &#124; Society|newspaper=The Guardian|author=Maria L La Ganga in Denver|accessdate=2016-07-10}}</ref>\n*** '''[[Misty Snow]]''' became the first openly transgender candidate to win a major party primary for the US Senate.<ref name=\"theguardian1\" />\n*** At the GOP Convention, '''[[Peter Thiel]]''' became the first person to publicly announce in a speech that he is gay,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/openly-gay-libertarian-tech-entrepreneur-peter-thiel-speak-rnc-n614191|title=Peter Thiel Makes History at RNC: 'I'm Proud to be Gay'|last=Margolin|first=Emma|date=2016|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=2016-07-22}}</ref> Rachel Hoff became the first openly gay person to sit on the Republican Party's Platform Committee,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/12/us/politics/rachel-hoff-gop-issues.html|title=G.O.P. Platform Committee Welcomes First Gay Member but Not Gay Marriage|date=2016|first=Jeremy W.|last=Peters|website=www.nytimes.com|accessdate=2016-07-11}}</ref> and [[Donald Trump]] became '''the first Republican nominee to mention the LGBT community in a GOP nomination address''', saying in his acceptance speech at the [[2016 Republican National Convention]] on 21 July 2016: \"As your president, I will do everything in my power to protect our LGBTQ citizens from the violence and oppression of a hateful foreign ideology.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/excited-trump-gay-republicans-struggle-rest-gop-40781225|title=Making GOP History, Trump Vows to Protect LGBTQ Community|date=22 July 2016|work=ABC News|author=Lederman, Josh|accessdate=31 July 2016}}</ref>\n*** '''[[Sarah McBride]]''' was a speaker at 