1\">{{cite web|last=Gilchrist |first=Tracy E. |url=https://www.advocate.com/theater/2019/8/05/prom-makes-broadway-herstory-ending-actual-same-sex-marriage |title=The Prom Makes Broadway Herstory by Ending in Actual Same-Sex Marriage |publisher=Advocate.com |date= 2019-08-05|accessdate=2019-08-06}}</ref>\n* '''Politics'''\n** [[Jacinda Ardern]] became '''the first prime minister of New Zealand to march in a gay pride parade.'''<ref>{{cite news|author=Eleanor Ainge Roy in Dunedin |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/feb/19/jacinda-ardern-becomes-first-new-zealand-pm-to-take-part-in-gay-pride-parade |title=Jacinda Ardern becomes first New Zealand PM to march in gay pride parade &#124; World news |newspaper=The Guardian |date=2018-02-17 |accessdate=2018-02-21}}</ref>\n** '''[[Toni Atkins]]''' succeeded [[Kevin de Le\u00f3n]] as [[President pro tempore of the California State Senate|Senate President Pro Tempore]]. This made her the first woman and the first openly [[LGBT]] person (she was a lesbian) to lead the California State Senate.<ref name = first>{{cite news|url=http://www.sacbee.com/news/politics-government/capitol-alert/article188586714.html|title= Toni Atkins will be first woman and the first openly gay person to lead California Senate|newspaper=Sacramento Bee|date=7 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"startribune.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.startribune.com/first-woman-lgbt-lawmaker-to-lead-california-senate/477578743/|title=First woman, LGBT lawmaker to lead California Senate|publisher=|access-date=24 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180324102909/http://www.startribune.com/first-woman-lgbt-lawmaker-to-lead-california-senate/477578743/|archive-date=24 March 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n** '''[[Christine Hallquist]] became the first openly transgender candidate for governor nominated by a major political party in the United States''' when she was nominated for governor of Vermont by the Democrats.<ref name=\"abcnews.go.com\">{{cite