f the Kansas congressional delegation, and the first openly gay person representing Kansas on the federal level.'''<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lowry |first1=Bryan |last2=Bergen|first2=Katy|title=Sharice Davids makes history: Kansas' 1st gay rep, 1st Native American woman in Congress |url=https://www.kansascity.com/news/politics-government/election/article221156115.html |accessdate=7 November 2018 |work=[[Kansas City Star]] |date=6 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/1808/23/cnr.02.html |title=CNN.com - Transcripts |publisher=Transcripts.cnn.com |date=2018-08-23 |accessdate=2018-11-07}}</ref>\n** [[Angie Craig]] became '''the first openly lesbian mother to be elected to the US Congress, and the first openly gay person elected to Congress from Minnesota.'''<ref name=\"huffingtonpost1\">{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/lgbtq-midterm-elections_us_5be29707e4b0dbe871a49ea0 |title=LGBTQ Candidates Record Historic Midterm Wins In Rainbow Wave &#124; HuffPost |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date= 2018-11-07|accessdate=2018-11-07}}</ref><ref name=\"instyle\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.instyle.com/news/angie-craig-first-lesbian-mom-congress|title=If She Wins, Angie Craig Will Be the First Lesbian Mom in Congress|magazine=InStyle|first=Romi|last=Oltuski|date=21 October 2018|accessdate=6 November 2018}}</ref>\n** '''Ahmad Zahra''' was elected to [[Fullerton, California|Fullerton]] city council, thus '''becoming the first openly gay Muslim to be elected to office in the USA'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dailytitan.com/2018/11/councilmen-silva-and-zahra-elected-to-fullerton-city-council/|title=Councilmen Silva and Zahra elected to Fullerton city council|date=7 November 2018|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/over-100-lgbti-people-elected-midterm-elections/#gs.Y_Kknlw |title=Over 100 LGBTI people won in yesterday's US midterm elections |publisher=Gaystarnews.com |date=2018-11-07 |accessdate=2018-12-20}}</ref>\n** '''[[Chris Pappas (politician)|Chris Pappas]]''' '''became the first openly gay person representing Congress for New Hampshire'''.<ref name=\"huffingtonpost1\"/>\n** [[Katie Hill (politician)|Katie Hill]] was elected as '''California's first openly bisexual person, and first openly queer woman, to be a member of Congress.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hrc.org/blog/ten-women-leaders-breaking-barriers-for-bisexual-representation |title=Ten Women Leaders Breaking Barriers for Bisexual Representation &#124; Human Rights Campaign |publisher=Hrc.org |date= |accessdate=2019-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Baume |first=Matt |url=https://www.intomore.com/impact/californias-katie-hill-makes-history-as-first-openly-bisexual-member-of-congress |title=Katie Hill Makes History As California's First Openly Bisexual Member of Congress |publisher=Intomore.com |date=2018-11-07 |accessdate=2019-03-16}}</ref>\n** '''[[Ricardo Lara]]''' was elected as California's insurance commissioner, making him the first openly gay person elected to statewide office in California's history.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ricardo Lara wins Insurance Commissioner race!|first=Karen|last=Ocamb|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Blade]]|date=16 November 2018 |url=https://www.losangelesblade.com/2018/11/16/ricardo-lara-wins-insurance-commissioner-race/|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref>\n** '''[[Megan Hunt (politician)|Megan Hunt]]''', who was openly bisexual,<ref name=blair>[http://www.enterprisepub.com/public/blair-native-wins-nebraska-legislature-district/article_a1b8f756-e44c-11e8-a934-dbff52d55deb.html \"Blair native wins Nebraska Legislature District 8\"]. ''[[Pilot-Tribune & Enterprise]]'', 8 November 2018.</ref> became the first openly LGBTQ person elected to the state legislature of Nebraska.<ref>[https://www.3newsnow.com/news/local-news/megan-hunt-becomes-first-openly-lgbtq-person-elected-to-legislature \"Megan Hunt becomes first openly LGBTQ person elected to legislature\"] [[KMTV]], 8 November 2018.</ref> \n* '''Trans'''\n**'''[[Angela Ponce]]''' made history on 29 June 2018 as the first openly transgender woman to be crowned [[Miss Spain]],<ref name=gmanetwork>{{cite web |url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/lifestyle/content/658755/miss-universe-spain-crowns-its-first-transgender-queen-angela-ponce/story/ |title=Miss Universe Spain crowns its first transgender queen, \u00c1ngela Ponce |last=Tantiangco |first=Aya |date=June 30, 2018 |website=gmanetwork.com |publisher=GMA Network |access-date=July 1, 2018}}</ref> and became the first openly transgender contested at Miss Universe.<ref name=\"WaPo2018-12-17a\">{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2018/12/17/miss-spain-becomes-first-transgender-woman-compete-miss-universe-pageant/?noredirect=on|title=Miss Spain makes history as first transgender woman to compete in Miss Universe pageant |author=Amy B Wang |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=18 December 2018 |date=17 December 2018 }}</ref><ref name=\"Time2018-12-17a\">{{cite magazine |url=http://time.com/5481417/miss-spain/|title=Miss Spain Made History as the First Miss Universe Transgender Competitor|first=Cady|last=Lang|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=18 December 2018 |date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n**[[Laverne Cox]] became '''the first openly transgender person to appear on the cover of any ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'' magazine (specifically, Cosmopolitan South Africa's February 2018 issue).'''.<ref name=\"Wong\"/>\n**[[Paris Lees]] became '''the first openly transgender woman featured in British ''[[Vogue (British magazine)|Vogue]]''.'''<ref name=\"bbc.com\"/>\n**''Transgender Health'' reported that a transgender woman in the United States breastfed her adopted baby; this was '''the first known case of a transgender woman breastfeeding.'''<ref>{{cite journal|title=Case Report: Induced Lactation in a Transgender Woman|first1=Tamar|last1=Reisman|first2=Zil|last2=Goldstein|j