in-go-gos-musical-head-over-heels |url-status=live}}</ref>\n**'''[[Christine Hallquist]] became the first openly transgender candidate for governor nominated by a major political party in the United States''' when she was nominated for governor of Vermont by the Democrats.<ref name=\"abcnews.go.com\"/>\n**'''[[Yance Ford]]''' and Joslyn Barnes were awarded an Emmy for Exceptional Merit in Documentary Filmmaking for producing ''[[Strong Island (film)|Strong Island]]'', which made Ford the first openly transgender man and the first black openly transgender person to win an Emmy award, as well as the first openly transgender filmmaker to win a [[Creative Arts Emmy]].<ref name=\"Intomore.com\"/><ref name=\"Emmys.com\"/><ref name=\"dl\"/>\n**'''Patricio Manuel''' became the first openly transgender male to box professionally in the United States, and, as he won the fight, the first openly transgender male to win a pro boxing fight in the U.S.<ref name=\"si.com\"/>\n**'''Colombia''' prosecuted a transgender woman's murder as a [[femicide]] for the first time in 2018, sentencing Davinson Stiven Erazo S\u00e1nchez to twenty years in a psychiatric center for \"aggravated femicide\" a year after he killed Anyela Ramos Claros, a transgender woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/latino/first-time-colombia-prosecutes-transgender-woman-s-murder-femicide-n950021 |title=For the first time, Colombia prosecutes a transgender woman's murder as a femicide |publisher=Nbcnews.com |date= |accessdate=2018-12-23}}</ref>\n\n==2019==\n<!--Please also add applicable entries to the List of lesbian, gay, bisexual, or transgender firsts by year article-->\n* '''Same-sex marriage laws''':\n**'''Came into effect''': [[Same-sex marriage in Austria|Austria]]\n**'''Passed and came into effect''': [[Same-sex marriage in Taiwan|Taiwan]] (first in Asia); Mexican states of [[Same-sex marriage in San Luis Potos\u00ed|San Luis Potos\u00ed]], [[Same-sex marriage in Hidalgo|Hidalgo]] and [[Same-sex marriage in Baja California Sur|Baja California Sur]]\n**'''Supreme court ruling''': [[Same-sex marriage in Ecuador|Ecuador]] and Mexican states of [[Same-sex marriage in Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Nuevo Le\u00f3n]] and [[Same-sex marriage in Aguascalientes|Aguascalientes]]\n*'''Civil union laws:'''\n**'''Came into effect:''' [[Recognition of same-sex unions in San Marino|San Marino]]\n**'''Passed:''' [[Recognition of same-sex unions in Monaco|Monaco]]\n**'''Court order not yet implemented and subject to appeal:''' [[Same-sex marriage in the Cayman Islands|Cayman Islands]]\n* '''Decriminalisation of homosexuality''': [[LGBT rights in Angola|Angola]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2019/01/23/angola-decriminalizes-same-sex-conduct |title=Angola Decriminalizes Same-Sex Conduct &#124; Human Rights Watch |publisher=Hrw.org |date= |accessdate=2019-02-28}}</ref> [[LGBT rights in Botswana|Botswana]]\n* '''Criminalisation of homosexuality passed or came into effect''': [[LGBT rights in Brunei|Brunei]], [[Gabon]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.openlynews.com/i/?id=62aa889f-1ba6-4694-ae10-f06febc7aa80|title=Gabon bans gay sex as global pace of reform falters|last=OPENLY|website=OPENLY|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref>\n* '''Equalization of age of consent''': [[LGBT rights in Canada|Canada]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.parl.ca/LegisInfo/BillDetails.aspx?Language=en&Mode=1&billId=9745407 |title=LEGISinfo - House Government Bill C-75 (42-1) |publisher=Parl.ca |date= |accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref>\n*'''Anti-Discrimination Laws:''' [[LGBT rights in San Marino|San Marino]] (constitutional amendment)\n*'''Politics:'''\n**'''US Politics:'''\n***[[Pete Buttigieg]] became '''the first ever openly gay Democratic presidential candidate in American history'''<ref>{{cite web|last=Schwab |first=Nikki |url=https://nypost.com/2019/01/23/pete-buttigieg-becomes-first-openly-gay-democrat-to-run-for-president/ |title=Pete Buttigieg is first openly gay Democrat to run for president |publi