019/04/23/tampa-mayor-election-follow-our-live-blog-for-the-latest/|title=Tampa mayor election: Jane Castor easily defeats David Straz in historic race|last1=Wilson|first1=Kirby|website=Tampa Bay Times|accessdate=24 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/win-tampa-ex-police-chief-jane-castor-becomes-florida-s-n997861|title=Tampa elects first out lesbian mayor, ex-police chief Jane Castor|last1=Fitzsimons|first1=Tim|date=23 April 2019|accessdate=25 April 2019|publisher=NBC News}}</ref>\n*** Utah County Commissioner Nathan Ivie came out as gay, making him '''the first openly gay Republican officeholder in Utah history.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/2019/05/27/gehrke-utah-now-has-its/|title=Gehrke: Utah now has its first openly gay Republican officeholder and his courage gives the state an opportunity to grow|website=The Salt Lake Tribune}}</ref>\n***'''Donald Trump''' became the first Republican president to acknowledge [[LGBT Pride Month]], which he did through tweeting.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/davidmack/trump-pride-month-tweet-anti-lgbt-record|title=Trump Marks Pride Month While Attacking LGBT Rights|author=Posted on 31 May 2019, at 5:04 p.m. ET|date=2019|publisher=Buzzfeednews.com|accessdate=2019-06-03}}</ref>\n***The governors of New York, Michigan, Wisconsin, Colorado, and California fly the LGBT pride flag from their state capitals or governor's office buildings for the first time during LGBT Pride Month.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rochesterfirst.com/news/local-news/lgbtq-pride-flag-raised-over-thestatecapitol-for-the-first-time-in-ny-state-history/2055297395|title=LGBTQ pride flag raised over the State Capitol for the first time in NY State history|date=5 Jun 2019|publisher=Rochesterfirst.com|accessdate=2019-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/state-watch/448754-pride-flags-fly-outside-michigan-state-build-in-historic-first|title=Pride flag