-first-openly-gay-candidate-in-tunisia-is-running-for-president/ |title=Mounir Baatour, First Openly Gay Candidate in Tunisia, is Running for President |publisher=Intpolicydigest.org |date=2017-09-28 |accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://stepfeed.com/lawyer-and-activist-to-become-first-gay-man-to-run-for-president-in-tunisia-5547|title=Lawyer and activist to become first gay man to run for president in Tunisia|first=Leyal|last=Khalife|date=4 July 2019|website=StepFeed}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/mounir-baatour-first-gay-man-president-tunisia/ |title=Lawyer Mounir Baatour becomes first gay man to run for President of Tunisia |publisher=Gaystarnews.com |date=2019-07-04 |accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref>\n***Serbian Prime Minister [[Ana Brnabi\u0107]]'s partner Milica \u0110ur\u0111i\u0107 gave birth to a boy; Brnabi\u0107 is therefore believed to be '''the first prime minister in a same-sex couple whose partner gave birth while the prime minister was in office.'''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/ana-brnabic-serbia-milica-djurdjic-baby-birth-son-gay-lgbt-same-sex-couple-a8790306.html|title=Gay partner of Serbian PM Ana Brnabic gives birth in first for a world leader|first=Peter|last=Stubley|date=2019|newspaper=The Independent|accessdate=2019-02-21}}</ref>\n***[[Gianmarco Negri]] was elected mayor of [[Tromello]], making him '''Italy's first openly transgender mayor.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/feature/nbc-out/italy-elects-its-first-transgender-mayor-n1010751|title=Italy elects its first transgender mayor|date=|publisher=Nbcnews.com|accessdate=2019-05-30}}</ref>\n*** In June 2019, [[President of Austria]] '''[[Alexander Van der Bellen]]''' became '''the first [[Head of State]] to address a [[EuroPride]] parade'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/EuroPride/status/1139944034909249536|title=Twitter|date=2019-06-15|publisher=Mobile.twitter.com|accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://wien.orf.at/stories/3000508/|title=Politik : Halbe Million bei Regenbogenparade|author=red, wien.ORF.at/Agenturen|date=2019-06-15|publisher=wien.ORF.at|accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref>\n*** In June, [[List of Ministers of Education (Austria)|Minister of Education, Science and Research]] [[Iris Eliisa Rauskala]] came out as [[lesbian]] and announced that she is married to a woman, thus becoming '''the first openly LGBT minister in the [[Government of Austria]].'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.queer.de/detail.php?article_id=33849|title=Rauskala kommt raus: Ministerin outet sich als lesbisch|date=|publisher=queer.de|accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.oe24.at/oesterreich/politik/Rauskala-Neue-Bildungsministerin-gibt-ihre-Homosexualitaet-bekannt/384611855|title=Rauskala: Neue Bildungsministerin gibt ihre Homosexualit\u00e4t bekannt|date=|publisher=M.oe24.at|accessdate=2019-07-08}}</ref>\n***'''[[Amir Ohana]]''' became the first openly gay person to be appointed as a minister in the Israeli government.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-5520991,00.html|title=Netanyahu names Amir Ohana as new justice minister|date=2019-05-06|website=The YnetNews|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n***'''[[Nitzan Horowitz]]''' successfully challenged incumbent [[Tamar Zandberg]] for the leadership of Meretz, which made Meretz the first Israeli party to elect an openly gay person as its leader.<ref name=\"Nitzan\">{{cite web|url=https://www.jta.org/quick-reads/israels-meretz-party-becomes-first-to-elect-an-openly-gay-leader|title=Israel's Meretz party becomes country's first to elect an openly gay leader - Jewish Telegraphic Agency|date=|publisher=Jta.org|accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Meretz-now-has-new-leader-Nitzan-Horowitz-593944|title=Israel's first gay party leader Nitzan Horowitz elected head of Meretzr (sic)|first=Jeremy|last=Sharon|date=27 June 2019|work=[[The Jerusalem Post]]|accessdate=27 June 2019}}</ref>\n***'''[[Boris Johnson]]''' becomes Prime Minister of the UK on 23 July 2019, becoming the first British Prime Minister to have attended a Pride Parade (in 2008 and 2010).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2010/jul/02/boris-johnson-gay-pride-london|title=Boris Johnson to attend London gay pride celebrations|author=H\u00e9l\u00e8ne Mulholland|date=2010-07-02|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=2020-03-12}}</ref>\n*** On 17 August 2019, in an op-ed to the ''[[Ottawa Citizen]]'', [[Jim Watson (Canadian politician)|Jim Watson]] announced that he was [[coming out of the closet]], becoming '''Ottawa's first openly gay mayor.'''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/opinion/columnists/mayor-jim-watson-after-40-years-im-opening-the-closet-door|title=Mayor Jim Watson: After 40 years, I\u2019m opening the closet door|author=Jim Watson Updated: 20 August 2019|date=2019-08-17|newspaper=Ottawa Citizen|accessdate=2019-08-22}}</ref>\n***'''[[Taiga Ishikawa]]''' was elected to the [[House of Councillors]] in the [[2019 Japanese House of Councillors election]], becoming the first openly-gay man to be elected to either chamber of the [[National Diet]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asahi.com/ajw/articles/AJ201907220044.html|title=Gay politician wins Upper House seat with LGBT support\uff1aThe Asahi Shimbun|date=|publisher=Asahi.com|accessdate=2019-07-23}}</ref>\n***'''[[Prince Harry, Duke of Sussex|Prince Harry]] and [[Meghan, Duchess of Sussex|Meghan Markle]]''' became the first British royals known to celebrate [[LGBT Pride Month]].<ref name=\"pinknews1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2019/06/03/prince-harry-meghan-marke-first-royals-celebrate-pride-month/|title=Prince Harry and Meghan Markle are first royals to celebrate Pride Month \u00b7 PinkNews|date=2019-03-11|publisher=Pinknews.co.uk|accessdate=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n*** \n*'''Arts and Culture:'''\n** On 23 August 2019, ''[[The New York Times]]'' reported a complaint against [[Anne McClain]] through the Federal Trade Commission accusing her of illegally accessing financial information while residing in the International Space Station.<ref name=\"Anne0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/23/us/nasa-astronaut-anne-mcclain.html|title=How a Bitter Divorce Battle on Earth Led to Claims of a Crime in Space|last=Baker|first=Mike|date=2019-08-23|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-08-24|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=\"Anne\">{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/08/23/politics/nasa-astronaut-bank-account-first-criminal-allegation-space/index.html|title=New York Times: Astronaut accessed estranged spouse's bank account in possible first criminal allegation from space|first=Caroline|last=Kelly|website=CNN|access-date=2019-08-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/nasa-astronaut-accused-hacking-her-estranged-spouse-s-bank-account-n1046061|title=A top NASA astronaut accused of hacking her estranged spouse's bank account from space|last=Acevedo|first=Nicole|date=24 August 2019|website=NBC News|language=en|access-date=2019-08-24}}</ref> This accusation \"outed\" McClain as a LGBT woman, making her '''the first openly LGBT NASA astronaut.'''<ref name=\"Bartels\">{{cite news|url=https://www.space.com/nasa-astronaut-anne-mcclain-space-crime-claim.html|title=A NASA Astronaut's Divorce Has Sparked Claims of a Crime in Space: Report|last=Bartels|first=Meghan|date=23 August 2019|work=Space.com|access-date=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n** '''[[Bernd M\u00f6nkeb\u00fcscher]]''' became the first Catholic priest in Germany who outed himself in public without problems by his bishop, in February 2019.<ref>[https://www.wa.de/nordrhein-westfalen/pfarrer-bernd-moenkebuescher-seiner-homosexualitaet-katholische-kirche-11746483.html Au\u00dfergew\u00f6hnlich ehrliche und offene Worte \u00fcber seine Homosexualit\u00e4t (german)], February 12, 2019</ref>\n