]]''\n| Himself (host)\n| Episode: \"Woody Harrelson/[[David Byrne]]\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 1990\n| ''[[Walt Disney anthology television series|Walt Disney's Wonderful World of Color]]''\n| Woody Boyd\n| Episode: \"Disneyland's 35th Anniversary Celebration\"\n|-\n| ''[[Mother Goose Rock 'n' Rhyme]]''\n| Lou the Lamb\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''Saturday Night Live''\n| Himself (host)\n| Episode: \"Woody Harrelson/[[Vanessa L. Williams]]\"\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[The Simpsons]]''\n| Woody Boyd (voice)\n| Episode: \"[[Fear of Flying (The Simpsons)|Fear of Flying]]\"\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Spin City]]''\n| Tommy Dugan\n| Episode: \"Meet Tommy Dugan\"\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Ellen (TV series)|Ellen]]''\n| Henry\n| Episode: \"Ellen: A Hollywood Tribute: Part 2\"\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Frasier]]''\n| Woody Boyd\n| Episode: \"[[The Show Where Woody Shows Up]]\"\n|-\n| 2001\u20132002\n| ''[[Will & Grace]]''\n| Nathan\n| 7 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Game Change (film)|Game Change]]''\n| [[Steve Schmidt]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''David Blaine: Real or Magic''\n| Himself\n| Television special\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014\n| ''[[True Detective]]''\n| Martin \"Marty\" Hart\n| 8 episodes; also executive producer\n|-\n| ''Saturday Night Live''\n| Himself (host)\n| Episode: \"Woody Harrelson/[[Kendrick Lamar]]\"\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2019\n| ''[[Live in Front of a Studio Audience]]''\n| [[Archie Bunker]]\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| ''Saturday Night Live''\n| Himself (host) / [[Joe Biden]]\n| 3 episodes\n|}\n\n===Theatre===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n|1985\u20131986\n|''[[Biloxi Blues]]''\n|Joseph Wykowski,<br> Roy Selridge (standbys)\n|[[Neil Simon Theatre]]\n|-\n|1987\u20131988\n|''[[The Boys Next Door (play)|The Boys Next Door]]''\n|Jack\n|[[Lamb's Theatre]]\n|-\n|1999\u20132000\n|''[[The Rainmaker (play)|The Rainmaker]]''\n|Bill Starbuck\n|[[Brooks Atkinson Theatre]]\n|-\n|2005\u20132006\n|''[[The Night of the Iguana]]''\n|Shannon\n|Lyric Theatre London\n|-\n|2012\n|''Bullet for Adolf''\n|{{n/a|Director and playwright}}\n|[[New World Stages|New World Stages Stage IV]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{|class = \"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Nominated work\n! Award\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1987\n| rowspan=7 | ''Cheers''\n| [[American Comedy Awards|American Comedy Award for Funniest Newcomer - Male or Female]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 1988\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 1989\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1990\n| [[American Comedy Awards|American Comedy Award for Funniest Supporting Male Performer in a TV Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 1991\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1992\n| rowspan=2 | ''White Men Can't Jump''\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss]] {{small|(shared with Rosie Perez)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo]] {{small|(shared with Wesley Snipes)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1993\n| rowspan=2 | ''Indecent Proposal''\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss]] {{small|(shared with [[Demi Moore]])}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Raspberry Award for Worst Supporting Actor]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1994\n| rowspan=2 |''Natural Born Killers''\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss]] {{small|(shared with [[Juliette Lewis]])}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[MTV Movie Award for Best On-Screen Duo]] {{small|(shared with Juliette Lewis)}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 1996\n| rowspan=3 | ''The People vs. Larry Flynt''\n| [[Academy Award for Best Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Drama]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Leading Role]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''Frasier''\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''A Prairie Home Companion''\n| [[Gotham Independent Film Award for Best Ensemble Cast]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''No Country for Old Men''\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Transsiberian''\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=20 | 2009\n| rowspan=13 | ''The Messenger''\n| [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Supporting Male]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[National Board of Review Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society]] Award for Body of Work\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Broadcast Film Critics Association Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Chicago Film Critics Association Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Detroit Film Critics Society]] Award for Best Supporting Actor\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Supporting Actor \u2013 Motion Picture]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Houston Film Critics Society]] Award for Best Supporting Actor\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Supporting Actor - Motion Picture]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]] for Best Supporting Actor\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=6 | ''Zombieland''\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society]] Award for Body of Work\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Scream Award]] for Best Ensemble\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Detroit Film Critics Society]] Award for Best Supporting Actor\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Detroit Film Critics Society Award for Best Cast\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[2010 Scream Awards|Scream Award for Best Horror Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''2012''\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society]] Award for Body of Work\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2011\n| rowspan=3 | ''Rampart''\n| [[African American Film Critics Association]] Award for Best Actor\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Male Lead]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award]] for Best Actor in a Motion Picture\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4| 2012\n| rowspan=4 | ''Game Change''\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award]] for Best Actor in a Movie/Miniseries\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Miniseries or a Movie]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Miniseries or Television Movie]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2014\n| rowspan=4 | ''True Detective''\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2015\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Miniseries or Television Film]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Actor \u2013 Television Series Drama]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 2018\n| rowspan=4 | ''Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri''\n| [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[BAFTA Award for Best Actor in a Supporting Role]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Male Actor in a Supporting Role]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]]\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{commons}}\n* {{IMDb name|437}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{Iobdb name|13375}}\n* [http://www.voiceyourself.com Profile], VoiceYourself.com\n* [http://www.emmys.com/celebrities/woody-harrelson Woody Harrelson profile], Emmys.com\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Woody Harrelson\n|list  =\n{{EmmyAward ComedySupportingActor}}